commit.message: Adding support for zstd, pzstd and mksquashfs using zstd/pzstd

pixz: don't add trailing index to tarballs

If pixz detects the input file is a tarball, it adds a trailing file index to help in seeking the file.
However, this trailing index is causes decompression errors with xz -d and systemd-importd.

For compatibility with these tools, force pixz to never add this tarball index.

pixz: don't add trailing index to tarballs

If pixz detects the input file is a tarball, it adds a trailing file index to help in seeking the file.
However, this trailing index is causes decompression errors with xz -d and systemd-importd.

For compatibility with these tools, force pixz to never add this tarball index.

_sub_other_options: always modify cmdargs as a list

cmdargs is always a list, but the list type does not have a .replace()
method. The if/else branches concern the type of the infodict's
other_options.

clean up pylint warnings

definitions.py: Add lzip, lzma, lzop definitions

Configure DEFAULT_TAR via os.uname()

instead of hard-coding.

Apply aditional patches from Yuta for bsd support bug 574422

Change the way decomp_opt changes were applied to the definitions.
Change from joining with "\t" back to " " and split accordingly.
Add additional docstrings.

Original Author: Yuta Satoh
X-Gentoo-bug: 574422
X-gentoo-bug-url: https://bugs.gentoo.org/show_bug.cgi?id=574422

Add comp_prog, other_otions to the basic definitions.

Add other_options to the non-xattr definitions to deprecate the *_x variants.
This also makes them more configurable with additional options.
Replace the hard-coded "-I" tar option with "%conp_prog)s" to be configurable for both
linux tar and bsd tar command options.
Add the missing arch option to the sqaushfs definition.
squashfs: make _xz and _gzip variants
Set version for the first release
Fix mixed case typo
Fix previous commit for possibility that Popen failed and stdout, stderr were none
Squelch stderr output, close PIPES

compress.py: Add a function to return an ordered list of file extensions

This is useful for ambiquos filenames and you want to search for existence of a file with
one of the file extensions tacked on to it.
This orders the list by the prefered search order passed in to it.
